longBusinessSummary: CPFL Energia S.A. engages in the generation, transmission, distribution, and commercialization of electricity to residential, industrial, and commercial customers in Brazil. The company generates electricity through hydro, wind, biomass, and solar resources. It also manufactures, rents, maintains, and commercializes mechanical equipment and services; and provides infrastructure and fleet, human resources, financial, supply and logistics, call center, IT, and telecommunication services. The company was incorporated in 1998 and is based in Campinas, Brazil. CPFL Energia S.A. is a subsidiary of State Grid Brazil Power Participações S.A.
